title: Multicultural Psychology
description: The impact of culture, ethnicity, and race on human behavior within the framework of psychological theory and research. Emphasis on ethnic minority groups within the U.S. including: African Americans, Native Americans, Asian Americans/Pacific Islanders, and Latino/a Americans. Not open to students in MS Psychology program. 4 seminars. Formerly PSY 472.
prerequisites: PSY 201 or PSY 202; and sophomore standing
